cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.HC, cs.SY. 

The paper presents a planning system for defining Partially Observable Markov Decision Processes (POMDPs) using an adaptive programming language. This involves aspects of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the use of POMDPs. The paper also focuses on the programming language aspect (cs.PL) and its application in the domain of human computation (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the transformation of programs into POMDPs, which could be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
